-- Google considers data center in Lithuania: report
-- 
-- Mon Jan 7, 2008 3:55am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/07/us-google-lithuania-idUSL0767120020080107

 

 VILNIUS  (Reuters) - Web search company Google Inc. is considering building a data center in Lithuania, business daily Verslo zinios reported on Monday. 

 The government has proposed locating the centre near a hydro power plant in Kaisiadoriu district, central Lithuania, and the negotiations over investment were to be closed soon, the paper said. The Lithuanian development agency, which is in charge of negotiating with potential investors, declined to comment. (Reporting by Nerijus Adomaitis; Editing by Quentin Bryar)